subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Clypeus with setose plate(s) delimited by sutures ( Fig. 26 , fig. 21 in
Schileyko et al . 2018
). Pretarsus of maxillae 2 apically pointed, with a ventral projection (as in C . ( T .) hephaestus Ázara & Ferreira, 2013 see their fig. 6C) or without it (as in adult (Rc 7502) of C . ( T .) sarasini furcatus ( Ribaut, 1923 )). Dorsal brush of maxilla 2 as long as or slightly longer than the corresponding pretarsus. Anterior margin of forcipular coxosternite bilobed, in most species with long enlarged marginal setae ( Fig. 26 ); tarsungula long, overlapping each other by at least 1/3 of their length when adducted. Sternites ( Fig. 32 ) with well-developed transverse thickening between coxae of legs; at least some anterior sternites with endosternites bordered by trigonal sutures, the configurations of these sutures may vary (see
Schileyko et al . 2018
). Anterior corners of the endosternite of some anterior sternites with lateral projections ( Fig. 32 ).

Number of species. 29 (
Schileyko et al. 2018
).
